📂 Day 2 – File Handling & Crontab (70 Commands)
🔹 File & Directory Handling (55 commands)
📄 File Creation & Viewing

touch file.txt → create empty file

cat file.txt → view file content

more file.txt → view with pagination

less file.txt → view file with scroll

head file.txt → first 10 lines

tail file.txt → last 10 lines

tail -f logfile.log → live monitoring

nano file.txt → open file in nano editor

vi file.txt → open file in vi editor

echo "Hello" > file.txt → write text to file

echo "World" >> file.txt → append text to file

stat file.txt → file details (size, permissions, etc.)

📁 Directory Operations

pwd → show current directory

ls → list files

ls -l → list with details

ls -a → show hidden files

ls -lh → list in human-readable sizes

cd dir → go inside directory

cd .. → go up one level

mkdir mydir → create directory

mkdir -p a/b/c → create nested dirs

rmdir mydir → remove empty directory

rm -r mydir → remove non-empty directory

📦 Copying, Moving, Deleting

cp file1.txt file2.txt → copy file

cp -r dir1 dir2 → copy directory

mv file1.txt newname.txt → rename file

mv file1.txt /path/ → move file

rm file.txt → delete file

rm -f file.txt → force delete

🔍 Searching & Filtering

find . -name file.txt → find file by name

find / -type d -name logs → find directory

grep "error" file.txt → search text in file

grep -i "error" file.txt → case-insensitive search

grep -r "error" . → recursive search in directory

grep -n "error" file.txt → show line numbers

📊 File Content Processing

wc file.txt → count lines, words, chars

wc -l file.txt → count lines only

wc -w file.txt → count words

wc -c file.txt → count characters

sort file.txt → sort file content

sort -r file.txt → reverse sort

uniq file.txt → remove duplicates

uniq -c file.txt → count duplicate occurrences

cut -d',' -f1 file.csv → cut first column

cut -c1-5 file.txt → extract first 5 characters

tr 'a-z' 'A-Z' < file.txt → convert to uppercase

tr -d 'a' < file.txt → remove all a

split -l 10 file.txt newfile → split into parts of 10 lines

cmp file1.txt file2.txt → compare files

diff file1.txt file2.txt → show file differences

🔐 Permissions & Ownership

ls -l → check permissions

chmod 644 file.txt → set read/write

chmod +x script.sh → make file executable

chown user file.txt → change file owner

chgrp group file.txt → change file group

⏰ Crontab & Scheduling (15 commands)
📋 Crontab Basics

crontab -e → edit crontab

crontab -l → list crontab jobs

crontab -r → remove crontab

crontab -u username -l → check another user’s jobs

🕒 Cron Job Timing Examples

* * * * * echo "Hello" >> cron.log → run every minute

0 * * * * echo "Hourly task" >> cron.log → run hourly

0 0 * * * echo "Daily task" >> cron.log → run daily

0 0 * * 0 echo "Weekly task" >> cron.log → run weekly

0 0 1 * * echo "Monthly task" >> cron.log → run monthly

0 6 * * 1-5 echo "Weekdays 6AM task" >> cron.log

📑 Special Cron Operators

@reboot echo "Run after reboot" >> cron.log

@hourly echo "Run every hour" >> cron.log

@daily echo "Run daily" >> cron.log

@weekly echo "Run weekly" >> cron.log

@monthly echo "Run monthly" >> cron.log
